  "intro": "The 2015-16 Columbus Blue Jackets season was the 16th season for the National Hockey League franchise that was established on June 25, 1997. Columbus hired head coach John Tortorella following the firing of Todd Richards, who started the season 0-8-0. The team began its regular season games on October 9, 2015 against the New York Rangers."
